<p>Once I had decided on a project I asked Rico to send me a couple more balls of the Essentials Super Chunky and the Fashion Light Luxury, I had a cowl design that would be super simple and use both yarns together. I have included the pattern below if you‚Äôd like to make your own.</p>

<h2 id="candyfloss-cowl-pattern"><strong>Candyfloss Cowl Pattern</strong></h2>

<h3 id="you-will-need">You will need:</h3>

<ul>
  <li>2 x balls of Rico Essentials Super Chunky (Shade 004 ‚Äì Lilac)</li>
  <li>2 x balls of Rico Fashion Light Luxury (Shade 022 ‚Äì Neon Fuchsia)</li>
  <li>9mm crochet hook</li>
</ul>

<p><img class="rounded img-fluid post-img mx-auto d-block" src="/assets/images/IMG_7273-2048x2048.jpeg" /></p>

<p><img class="rounded img-fluid post-img mx-auto d-block" src="/assets/images/FFC1CBBB-D125-4C46-9348-CAB7AD62DDCA-2048x2048.jpg" /></p>

<h3 id="terms">Terms:</h3>

<ul>
  <li>ch ‚Äì Chain</li>
  <li>tr ‚Äì Treble crochet (US Double Crochet)</li>
  <li>ss ‚Äì Slip Stitch</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="pattern">Pattern:</h3>

<p>To make the cowl you will be holding both yarns together at the same time. From row 2 onwards you will be working your stitches in the space between stitches rather than in the top of them.</p>

<p>Holding both yarns together loosely chain 25.</p>

<p>Row 1 ‚Äì tr into the 4th ch from the hook, tr along to the end, turn. (23 trs)</p>

<p>Row 2 ‚Äì 2ch, tr across (in between the stitches) to end, turn.</p>

<p>Row 3 to 33 ‚Äì Repeat row 2, fasten off and break yarn (leaving a long tail to finish the cowl).</p>

<p>Holding wrong sides together whip stitch together through back loops only, this creates a lovely neat join.</p>

